author: djames
msg: Update APR datatype definitions to be more portable, so that they will
work on platforms with non-standard integer sizes.
(apr_byte_t, apr_uint16_t, apr_uint32_t, apr_size_t): Use unsigned long
(apr_off_t, apr_int64_t): Use portable long long typemap.
(apr_uint64_t): Use portable unsigned long long typemap.

author: djames
msg: Upgrade Python "long" and "long long" typemaps to correctly handle integers of
any size (up to 64 bits). Use new typemaps to handle other types of integers.
(long, unsigned long): New typemaps, which can handle any integer which can
(long long, unsigned long long): New typemaps, which can handle any integer
(short, int, ssize_t, enum SWIGTYPE, svn_boolean_t, apr_seek_where_t,
(unsigned char, unsigned short, unsigned int, size_t): Use long typemap.

author: djames
msg: (long long): Use apr_int64_t in place of PY_LONG_LONG.
